==English==
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/jɛlp/}}
** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-yelp.wav|Audio (Southern England)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɛlp|s=1}}
===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|ȝelp}}, {{m|enm|yelp}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġielp|t=boasting, arrogance, pride}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*gelpą|t=boasting}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*gʰel-|t=to shout}}.
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# An [[abrupt]], high-pitched [[noise]] or [[utter]]ance.
#: ''The puppy let out a '''yelp''' when I stepped on her tail.''
# A type of emergency vehicle [[siren]] sounding quicker and more intense than the [[wail]].
