===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|en|enm|ȝelpen}}, {{m|enm|yelpen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġielpan|t=to boast}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*gelpaną}}. Compare {{cog|stq|jalpe||to bleep; cheep}}.
====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# To utter an abrupt, high-pitched [[noise]].
#: ''The children '''yelped''' with delight as they played in the cold water.''
